 right hand side to support the swinging arm. ","Engage ","service tool T3880104"," in the slots of the frame adjuster sleeve and rotate anticlockwise to loosen the sleeve fully.","Frame adjuster","T3880104 - Swinging Arm Adjuster Wrench","From the left hand side, disconnect the engine earth strap.","Disconnect the crankcase breather hose.","Hose clips","Engine breather pipe","Remove the rider’s left hand control plate.","Fixings","Control plate","Place a support beneath the engine and ensure that the frame is still adequately and securely supported.","Release the engine mounting nuts. Collect the nuts and washers, leaving the bolts in position.","Remove the left hand cylinder head mounting bolt.","Using ","service tool T3880377"," release the:","Rear cylinder head mounting adjuster on the left side of the frame,","Upper rear crankcase mounting adjuster,","Lower rear crankcase mounting adjuster,","Left hand cylinder head mounting adjuster.","Remove the right hand cylinder head mounting bolt.","Remove the remaining mounting bolts, collecting the spacer from the lower crankcase mounting bolt.","Two brake lines are attached to the brake line tidy on the rear of the crankcase.","Failure to detach the brake lines from the brake line tidy will cause damage to the braking system.","Detach the brake lines from the brake line tidy and position away from the crankcase.","Brake line from ABS modulator to front master cylinder","Brake line from ABS modulator to front brake caliper","Brake line tidy","Lower the engine away from the frame, taking care to avoid damage to the brake pipes.","When the engine has been removed, check to ensure that the brake line is attached to the ABS modulator bracket as shown in the following illustration. Rectify if necessary.","ABS brake line","Retaining clips","ABS modulator bracket"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType05","createdAt":"2024-06-13T07:25:17.675Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-13T07:25:17.675Z","__v":0}